tyle="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was Ichabob after he was finally declared "abandoned" and we were allowed to pick him up. His owner continually claimed that he "just hadn't moved the dog to the new house yet". Ichabob was left to starve for several weeks...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tg63jCG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is Ichabob now after he came to our shelter and I nursed him back to health. He's been trained in loose leash walking, sit, and down. He's an excellent dog!! But because we are a city run shelter we are required to euthanize if we run out of space. We've never had to before, something we're very proud of, but now people can't afford the time or money for dogs they adopted during covid. They're trying to surrender to us in droves for all kinds of reasons. Additionally dogs that people couldn't afford to or didn't want to spay/neuter have started causing oceans of dumped puppies to start coming into the shelter. We have no more space. We've been overworked and underfunded for weeks and rescues have stopped pulling our dogs. Ichabob is next up to be euthanized and we may have no choice. I'm desperately fighting but no one in our city wants to adopt anymore. Please if you're near/around the Jasper, TX area and have a rescue or can give our boy a home, let me know!! I don't want to lose him to the irresponsible actions of humans!

EDIT: Thank you everyone! I've been trying for so long to get this kind of attention on Ichabob, I've been crying tears of joy from all this support. Unfortunately I can't keep up with replying to all the comments (especially on my crap rural Texas wifi) but know that I see your rescue recommendations and add them to my list!! 

For those asking, donations unfortunately won't help Ichabob's perdicament, but they will be used to pay for medical bills and better equipment if you still want to donate. DM me for more details!! 

For those asking about adoption, DM me so I can find you in this sea of beautiful comments!! I can tell you all the info I know about the boy.

For those of you offering transport- you are angels. Thank you. All of you.

WE'LL GET THIS BOY A HOME!!! I'LL UPDATE AS SOON AS IT HAPPENS!!

EDIT 2 for anyone who is requesting an update. Newton, the county next to us, took in a huge surge of intakes from a hording case and had to pay for them to fly to a rescue in Maryland. There was room on the plane so they offered to take some of our pups too. If it all works out, there will be a significant release of pressure on getting Ichabob out ASAP. Unfortunately he can't go with because of his intense resource guarding. The rescue requested dogs with small or no behavioral problems.

It probably won't last long due to the huge waiting list we already have, but it at least gives me Monday to work with my supervisor on seeing if we can adopt him to someone on here. It will also give me time to bombard rescues with messages. If all else fails I will adopt the boy myself and send him on a road trip to someone! I won't give up on him!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ATVf7Cr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bathmathy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Now that my fake-ass rant is out and about, and one of my posts from today is causing people to make random comments that no one will actually read, we can get back to the actually important posts.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/hqSit4w</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pJrXoQq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/hqSit4w</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ThunderBashie]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Eddie drawing by my daughter. She's 13! Give her some love?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/MnNrdyP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Kh2JhgO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/MnNrdyP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[StarchySticks]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>May the force be…</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/L3JaaH6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rBiiyOY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/L3JaaH6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[persephonesmuse]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The old lady</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gQ3j25D</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/c48ewmt.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The movie is The Other Guy